# Build-context exclusions for `docker build` from the repo root.
#
# The container image Dockerfiles in infra/docker/ COPY explicit paths, so this list is
# about (a) keeping the context small/fast and (b) preventing host-only artifacts from
# being uploaded to the build daemon. Anything secret-bearing (e.g., `.env`) MUST be
# excluded here even though it is never COPY'd into the image — the build context is
# uploaded to the daemon in full.

# Secrets and local environment
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# VCS metadata
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Editor / IDE
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
*.swo

# Python virtualenvs and caches (generated locally; rebuilt inside the image)
**/.venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.mypy_cache
**/.pytest_cache
**/.ruff_cache

# Node / pnpm (Web image rebuilds these inside its own builder stage)
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/.pnpm-store

# Build output and coverage
**/dist
**/build
**/coverage

# Docker tooling
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.*.yml
infra/docker/*.dockerignore

# Top-level docs and Kiro spec metadata — not needed for any image build
.kiro
docs
README.md
LICENSE
